THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 118A of NRS is hereby amended by
2 adding thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. A landlord of a premises comprising more than 100
4 dwelling units attached to a single parcel of property shall
5 establish:
6 (a) A policy requiring an applicant for employment with the
7 landlord to undergo a criminal background check as a condition
8 of employment if the position for which the applicant is applying
9 entails access to any dwelling unit key; and
10 (b) Written policies and procedures regarding the:
11 (1) Storage, issuance, return and security of dwelling unit
12 keys; and
13 (2) If applicable, the usage and deactivation of dwelling
14 unit keys.
15 2. A landlord shall maintain on the premises a log that
16 accounts for the issuance and return of each dwelling unit key
17 and the written policies and procedures established pursuant to
18 paragraph (b) of subsection 1.
19 3. As used in this section:
20 (a) “Dwelling unit key” means any physical or electronic
21 mechanism used to gain access to a dwelling unit, including,
22 without limitation, a combination or access code.
23 (b) “Financial institution” means any bank, savings and loan
24 association, savings bank, thrift company, credit union or
25 financial institution that is licensed, registered or otherwise
26 authorized to do business in this State.
27 (c) “Landlord” means a landlord of a premises comprising
28 more than 100 dwelling units attached to a single parcel of
29 property. The term does not include a financial institution, real
30 estate broker, real estate broker-salesperson or real estate
31 salesperson.
32 (d) “Real estate broker” has the meaning ascribed to it in
33 NRS 645.030.
34 (e) “Real estate broker-salesperson” has the meaning ascribed
35 to it in NRS 645.035.
36 (f) “Real estate salesperson” has the meaning ascribed to it in
37 NRS 645.040.
